<TEXT>
typhoon ofelia was downgraded to a 
tropical storm on sunday a day after it slammed into eastern 
taiwan with 85 mph winds killing seven people and leaving 35 
others missing 
the storm also left 30 people dead in the philippines 
on sunday ofelia was bearing down on the chinese province of 
zhejiang but its winds had weakened to 50 mph forecasters said 
taiwan police said seven people drowned or died in landslides 
and 35 others were missing in and around the eastern coastal city 
of hualien 124 miles southeast of taipei 
most of the missing were swept away by floods that inundated 
more than 200 homes in villages police said some villages were 
under three feet of water and authorities estimated property and 
crop damage at more than 36 million 
two panamanian ships were pounded by ofelia off hualien on 
saturday 
the 10890ton freighter cahaya broke up into three sections in 
heavy seas police reported its 24member indonesian crew was 
rescued they said 
another 28 crewmen from the panamanian freighter juliana were 
rescued when their 7000ton vessel broke loose from its moorning 
and ran aground the officials said 
taiwan police said air and road links in the county were 
disrupted by landslides and flooding from the storm they reported 
that 18 inches of rain was recorded in one area in a 24hour span 
authorities canceled all domestic flights 
ofelia also buffeted the islands north and south with strong 
winds but no damage or casualties were reported 
the storm forced 84600 people to flee their homes in the 
philippines as it swept through luzon island with rain and strong 
winds according to the red cross and other relief agencies 
the hardesthit community in the philippines was la union 150 
miles northwest of manila where at least 22 people drowned or were 
crushed to death in landslides relief officials said 
in pangasinan west of la union two people were electrocuted 
in the manila suburb of pasig three children died when a concrete 
wall collapsed on their shanty officials said a 4yearold girl 
died in a landslide in the mountain resort city of baguio 
two other people were killed by lightning during a thunderstorm 
unleashed by ofelia in lanao del sur province on mindanao island 
about 520 miles south of manila 
</TEXT>
