<TEXT>
iranian authorities fear that the death toll in 
thursdays devastating earthquake may reach 50000 a senior un 
relief official said sunday 
previous figures on the number of deaths had varied but 
officials had said earlier an estimated 40000 were feared dead 
mhamed essaafi also said parts of the stricken area were still 
inaccessible because roads in the caspian sea region were blocked 
by landslides and rain 
essaafi spoke at a press briefing after meeting with the head of 
the iranian mission to the un office in geneva ambassador sirous 
nasseri he said nasseri again stressed that iran was more urgently 
in need of relief supplies than in rescue personnel 
he said the number of injured was still believed to be about 
100000 but there was no confirmed figure yet he said the 
homeless numbered about half a million 
about 6000 injured people are being treated in tehran 
hospitals according to the iranian authorities hospitals in the 
affected provinces are filled to capacity essaafi added quoting 
official iranian reports 
essaafi named by un secretary general javier perez de cuellar 
to oversee the international earthquake relief effort said he did 
not think there was any effort by the iranians to underreport the 
casualty figure 
an iranian resistance movement mujahedeen khalq had made such 
an accusation 
essaafi said that during the next two days at least 32 relief 
flights from nine countries were scheduled to land at tehran 
airport 
he said they included 11 planes from west germany carrying 145 
tons of supplies plus a field hospital with two medial teams and 
nine flights from turkey 
other flights announced to the office of the un disaster 
relief coordinator undro were to arrive from bangladesh japan 
canada cuba czechoslovakia pakistan switzerland and britain he 
said 
iran also asked for help from un experts in improving 
communications which continued to pose problems in the quake zone 
the international red cross said friday iran expressly stated it 
did not want satellite communications equipment to be included in 
the relief supplies 
the un official who will leave for tehran on monday said 
that the situation was being handed rather well by iran 
since the predawn quake on thursday more than 200 aftershocks 
have hit the region the biggest registering 42 on the richter 
scale and rocking the tarome olia region about 125 miles northwest 
of tehran the official islamic republic news agency said 
thursdays quake was at least 73 on the richter scale 
