the democrats campaign to unseat 
republican gov kay orr has taken a detour by way of the 
courtroom to decide a primary election cliffhanger 
unofficial tallies from a recount in may 15s closestever 
democratic primary election showed ben nelson with a 32vote lead 
over bill hoppner but the state board of canvassers has not 
certified the results 
last week the board ordered 23 of the states 93 counties to 
count by hand some ballots that machines had read as having no vote 
in the race the additional counting was expected to begin this 
week 
but nelson an omaha lawyer has asked the nebraska supreme 
court to order the board to certify the results and declare him the 
primary winner hoppner a former aide to sen bob kerrey dneb 
faced a monday deadline for filing a challenge to the election 
the situation has left mrs orr who has received high 
disapproval ratings in recent polls wondering against whom she 
should campaign 
research is difficult acknowledged scott matter mrs orrs 
campaign manager what do you do spend your mornings on hoppner 
and afternoons on nelson 
