the rowing stone entered by michigan 
state university swamped the competition to win the american 
society of civil engineers third annual national concrete canoe 
competition this weekend 
the winners beat 19 other schools to win a 5000 scholarship 
for the civil engineering department from contest sponsor master 
builders inc of cleveland 
the champions took the title saturday night after the second 
phase of the competition which involved races of 100 meters and 
200 meters on st ritas lake at the state university of new york 
buffalo 
the first phase oral and written presentations of the canoe 
designs was held friday and counted for 60 percent of team points 
the university of maryland finished second to earn a 2500 
scholarship while the university of california berkeley took 
third and a 1500 scholarship 
the fourthplace finisher the university of texas austin and 
fifthplace finisher the university of wisconsin milwaukee will 
receive commemorative plaques 
the canoes are judged on design construction speed and 
maneuverability the contest is designed both to give student 
engineers a chance to put classroom theories into practice and 
demonstrate how concrete can be used to construct a floating vessel 
