said mead township trustee gregg warren 
people in this town take care of their own theyve always 
been leery of outsiders said warren whose village of 4300 has 
lost at least 23 lives and scores of homes and businesses from a 
flash flood june 14 ten people are missing 
there was plenty of food clothing and volunteerism here 
before any of these outside organizations came in he said the 
local tv stations have raised a quarter of a million dollars around 
here banks have put up thousands of dollars contractors have 
donated the equipment and labor 
adversity is no stranger to shadyside where the slumping steel 
