president bush proposed the talks dubbed the structural 
impediments initiative last july to help cut japans massive 
trade imbalance with the united states 
the talks are aimed at reforming business practices and policies 
that are believed to act as structural trade and investment 
barriers 
in an interim report in april washington committed itself to 
cutting the federal budget deficit encouraging savings curbing 
