mr mandela is a working statesman said roger wilkins 
national coordinator of mandelas visit this is a visit to 
official washington really 
during his threeday stay he also will speak to 19000 people 
at a soldout rally at the washington convention center and visit 
labor leaders 
in advance of mandelas arrival assistant secretary of state 
herman cohen told reporters that bush and other us officials are 
eager to hear mandelas view on how he envisions a postapartheid 
society in south africa 
the main emphasis of the meeting with bush is negotiations 
and how to we help promote negotiations cohen said 
the anc and the de klerk government held their first talks last 
month over obstacles to negotiations for a new constitution 
